  "texts": [
    "Many people who live for a time in another country, or study their wisdom literature in depth, find that their trust in their own beliefs is undermined.",
    "It is common to think, \"I would have had different beliefs if I had grown up in a different place, and it is an accident of history that I have the beliefs I have.",
    "I could have been Hindu, Muslim, Buddhist, Christian, atheist, or many other things.\"",
    "The same line of thought applies to philosophical positions and attitudes about political arrangements.",
    "I am a believer in libertarian free will but I could have been a determinist."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}